<P>
2ND BAG OF $758,000 FOUND IN JAPAN THICKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man gathering bamboo shoots stumbled onto a bag with $758,000 in cash Sunday 
in the same thicket where a similar find was made five days earlier, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Officials still aren't sure how the two bags with identical amounts of cash 
ended up in the bamboo thicket 35 feet off a road in Kawasaki, southwest of 
Tokyo. Police suggested earlier that the first bag may have come from a crime. 
</P>
