<HEADLINE>
<P>
DORAN SCORES TWO GOALS, GIVES LAZERS DOUBLE OVERTIME VICTORY OVER WICHITA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Daryl Doran scored at 4:46 of the second overtime Sunday to give the Los 
Angeles Lazers a 5-4 victory over the Wichita Wings in the Major Indoor Soccer 
League regular-season finale before an announced crowd of nearly 3,000 at the 
Forum. 
</P>
<P>
Wichita's Mike Fox scored with nine seconds left in the fourth quarter to tie 
the game, 4-4, and force sudden-death overtime. Neither team scored during the 
first 15-minute overtime period. 
</P>
<P>
The Lazers finished the season with a 21-27 record and missed the playoffs, 
while Wichita finished 23-25 and moves on to post-season play. 
</P>
<P>
Doran had two goals for the Lazers. Poli Garcia, Ben Collins and Hector 
Marinaro also scored for Los Angeles. Fox had two goals for the Wings. Also 
scoring for Wichita were Erik Rasmussen and Chico Borja. 
</P>
<P>
The Wings outshot the Lazers, 38-36. Lazer goaltender Kris Peat had 19 saves 
while two Wichita goalies, Chris Vaccaro and Nenad Zigante, had a total of 14 
saves. 
</P>
