<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
$6.7 MILLION IS WAITING FOR LUCKY LOTTO PLAYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A lottery ticket bought in Huntington Beach will bring $6,733,161 to the owner, 
state lottery officials said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Two players had the six winning "Lotto 6-49" numbers and will split a 
$13,466,322 jackpot, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Lottery officials said the winning tickets were bought in Huntington Beach and 
Alameda. 
</P>
<P>
The numbers drawn Saturday night were 5, 49, 24, 36, 41, 9 and the bonus 
number, 7. Winners' names are not known until they turn in their tickets. 
</P>
<P>
Seven tickets had five regular numbers and the bonus; the buyers each won 
$298,327. The tickets were bought in Paramount, Escondido, Coronado, Roseville, 
Auburn, San Pablo and Cupertino. 
</P>
<P>
There were 271 tickets with five numbers, each winning $3,970, while 16,670 
tickets had four numbers, to win $58 each. Another 324,262 players picked three 
numbers, good for $5 each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
