<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ford Mexico Plant to Retool: The Ford Motor Co. assembly factory in Hermosillo 
will suspend operations for six months starting in August to retool for 
production of a new model car, the Mexico City newspaper La Jornada reported. 
The plant, which assembles the Tracer Mercury GT-18 for export to the United 
States and Canada, will convert its assembly lines to produce the Ford CT-20, 
auto workers union leader Dario Aguilar Tapia was quoted as saying. Production 
will increase from 32 to 40 vehicles per hour and average about 50,000 a year. 
The plant's 1,200 workers will receive full salaries during the suspension. 
