BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canadians to Bid for Jerusalem Post: Canadian investors headed by Charles 
Bronfman and British publisher Robert Maxwell will make a joint bid for the 
Jerusalem Post, Israel's English-language daily, a spokesman for the two said. 
Bronfman's Claridge group and Maxwell, chairman of Maxwell Communication Corp., 
are bidding for the controlling 55% stake in the left-leaning Post, owned by a 
subsidiary of Israel's troubled Koor Industries. The Maxwell-Bronfman group, 
refused to disclose the amount of the offer to be submitted today. The Post 
does not make a profit and its daily circulation of about 28,000 is among the 
smallest of the secular Israeli newspapers but it is read by government 
leaders, diplomats, the foreign media, English-speaking Israelis and 
Palestinians and visiting Jews. A weekly international edition reaches 60,000 
readers. 
</P>
