<TEXT>
<P>
Matsushita Electric Industrial Co. has officially rejected a Soviet request to 
produce videocassette recorders in the Soviet Union, company officials said 
today. 
</P>
<P>
The Soviet Electronic Industry Ministry asked Matsushita in late 1987 to start 
local VCR production by assembling such finished parts as cylinders exported 
from Japan, the officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Matsushita has so far exported finished VCRs to the Soviet Union. 
